|Inferences={{Inference
|Inference.Description=For infectious diseases, initially the disease is not in the patient.  
At start, disease enters the patient.
During ongoing, the extent of the disease within patient may increase or decrease (spread or shrink).
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=The effect the disease has on the patient is related to the extent of the disease/infection (e.g. the larger the extent of the disease, the worse the condition of the patient).
}}
